1 A RESOLUTION adjourning the Senate in honor and loving memory of Mack Lee
2 Wallace and Wilma June Wallace.
3 WHEREAS, Mack Lee Wallace was born on March 17, 1930, in Pulaski County,
4 Kentucky, to the late Ernest Lee Wallace and Dorothy Jane Wallace. Wilma June
5 Wallace was born on June 19, 1931, in Bracken County, Kentucky, to the late Harry
6 Walter Wagel and Carrie Mabel Wagel; and
7 WHEREAS, Mack Wallace was a 1947 graduate of Shopville High School and
8 Wilma Wallace was a 1951 graduate of Bracken County High School. After high school,
9 they both attended Eastern Kentucky University (EKU) and met on campus; and
10 WHEREAS, Mack and Wilma Wallace were married in Georgetown, Ohio, on
11 March 30, 1956; and
12 WHEREAS, Mack Wallace graduated from EKU in 1953 with a Bachelor of
13 Science in Elementary Education and Agriculture, and went on to receive his Master of
14 School Administration and Specialist in School Administration from the University of
15 Cincinnati. Wilma Wallace graduated from EKU in 1955 with a Bachelor of Science
16 Degree in Home Economics. She later earned a graduate degree from Morehead State
17 University; and
18 WHEREAS, both dedicated educators, Mack and Wilma Wallace had accomplished
19 careers. Upon their retirements in 1992, they had cumulatively served 81 years in public
20 schools in Ohio and Kentucky. Mack Wallace taught elementary and junior high school,
21 served as an elementary principal, and a superintendent. Wilma Wallace taught home
22 economics for the entirety of her career; and
23 WHEREAS, Mack and Wilma Wallace were also entrepreneurs. For 33 years, from
24 1981 to 2014, they owned Jeans and Such Clothing Store on Main Street in Augusta,
25 Kentucky. Mack Wallace also owned the Parkview Hotel and Creamy Freeze in Augusta,
26 and was a realtor for Perry Poe Real Estate in Brooksville, Kentucky; and
27 WHEREAS, Mack and Wilma Wallace were both members of the Augusta
