1 Christian Church, where Mack Wallace served as a trustee, elder, Sunday school teacher,
2 and Sunday school superintendent; and
3 WHEREAS, Mack and Wilma Wallace were dedicated to serving their community.
4 They were friends of the Augusta Independent Educational Foundation, members of the
5 Augusta Rotary Club, Bracken County Retired Teachers Association, Bracken County
6 Chamber of Commerce, Augusta Eastern Star Chapter #362, and pioneer members of the
7 EKU Alumni Association; and
8 WHEREAS, Mack Wallace served a four-year term as a magistrate in Bracken
9 County, was a board member of the Bracken County Ambulance Service, the Augusta
10 Ferry Board, the Licking Valley Community Action Program, and the Knoedler
11 Memorial Library, and was a member of Save Historic Augusta Restoration Effort and
12 the Buffalo Trace Manpower Council. Wilma Wallace was a member of the Bracken
13 County Extension Homemakers; and
14 WHEREAS, Mack Wallace was a 71-year Masonic Fraternity member. He was a
15 life member of the Burnside Lodge #634 and a member of the Augusta Lodge #80.
16 Brother Mack was a 32nd Degree Scottish Rite Mason and a Shriner; and
17 WHEREAS, Wilma Wallace departed this earthly life on September 14, 2024.
18 Mack Wallace passed away on November 21, 2024. They were married for 68 years; and
19 WHEREAS, Mack and Wilma Wallace were preceded in death by their parents and
20 youngest daughter, Melinda Wallace Thornberry. Mack Wallace was also preceded in
21 death by his sisters, Faye Bill (Robert) Bristol and Ina Nell (Charles) Sexton; brothers,
22 Leonard Barnes "LB" (Linda) Wallace and Gary Roger "Chuck" Wallace; and brother-in-
23 law: James Gayhart; and
24 WHEREAS, Mack and Wilma Wallace are survived by their eldest daughter, Amy
25 (Jeffrey) Jones; two granddaughters, Kelly (Austin) Miller and Kara (Sullivan) Simpson;
26 two great-grandsons, Walker Miller and Brooks Simpson; son-in-law, Mark Thornberry;
27 and Mack Wallace's sister, Mary Dean Gayheart;
